00:16:59.118 --> 00:17:01.654 align:middle
That means improved performance
for your applications

00:17:01.654 --> 00:17:03.489 align:middle
and better battery life.

00:17:03.489 --> 00:17:06.791 align:middle
But the benefits of
Metal don't stop there.

00:17:06.791 --> 00:17:10.463 align:middle
Metal's also great for
high-performance apps.

00:17:10.463 --> 00:17:14.500 align:middle
In fact, Metal combines
the compute power of OpenCL

00:17:14.500 --> 00:17:15.968 align:middle
and the graphics power of OpenGL

00:17:15.968 --> 00:17:21.007 align:middle
in a higher performance
API that does both.

00:17:21.007 --> 00:17:22.340 align:middle
And what we've seen from working

00:17:22.340 --> 00:17:26.078 align:middle
with early pro developers
is really phenomenal.

00:17:26.078 --> 00:17:28.314 align:middle
Adobe came in and,
in short order,

00:17:28.314 --> 00:17:31.684 align:middle
was able to deliver an
eight times improvement

00:17:31.684 --> 00:17:35.054 align:middle
in their rendering effects
inside of After Effects,

00:17:35.054 --> 00:17:37.990 align:middle
and they have been able
to take the drawing engine

00:17:37.990 --> 00:17:41.594 align:middle
in Illustrator, move it on top
of Metal, and take kinds of UI

00:17:41.594 --> 00:17:44.797 align:middle
that previously was
noninteractive,

00:17:44.797 --> 00:17:47.700 align:middle
like zoom of extremely
detailed drawings,

00:17:47.700 --> 00:17:49.669 align:middle
and make it completely flawless

00:17:49.669 --> 00:17:52.271 align:middle
and interactive,
thanks to Metal.

00:17:52.271 --> 00:17:54.707 align:middle
Adobe is so pleased with this
