01:07:57.373 --> 01:08:02.345 align:middle
[Cheers and applause]

01:08:02.345 --> 01:08:03.813 align:middle
You all know that the growth

01:08:03.813 --> 01:08:07.417 align:middle
that Swift has been experiencing
is just unprecedented,

01:08:07.417 --> 01:08:09.519 align:middle
and we've all seen
it with the flood

01:08:09.519 --> 01:08:12.789 align:middle
of applications coming
in to the App Store.

01:08:12.789 --> 01:08:18.094 align:middle
Well, now we are stepping on
the gas this year with Swift 2.

01:08:18.094 --> 01:08:21.430 align:middle
Now, Swift was designed from
the beginning to be fast,

01:08:21.430 --> 01:08:22.832 align:middle
and we've continued to roll

01:08:22.832 --> 01:08:26.769 align:middle
out targeted optimizations all
year long, and now with Swift 2,

01:08:26.769 --> 01:08:29.939 align:middle
we have an all-new optimization
technology that's especially

01:08:29.939 --> 01:08:33.408 align:middle
great for complex applications
and object-oriented programming

01:08:33.408 --> 01:08:36.412 align:middle
that we call Whole
Module Optimization,

01:08:36.412 --> 01:08:39.816 align:middle
and the results are
really fantastic.

01:08:39.816 --> 01:08:42.452 align:middle
In addition, we are bringing
the language features

01:08:42.452 --> 01:08:44.354 align:middle
that you've asked for most,

01:08:44.354 --> 01:08:46.522 align:middle
an elegant new error
handling model,

01:08:46.522 --> 01:08:48.323 align:middle
the ability to see
your interfaces

01:08:48.323 --> 01:08:51.894 align:middle
as synthesized headers
in Xcode, and the feature

01:08:51.894 --> 01:08:56.399 align:middle
that Tim has been begging for
all year, protocol extensions.

01:08:56.399 --> 01:08:59.102 align:middle
You are all going to love it.

01:08:59.102 --> 01:09:04.607 align:middle
Now, we think Swift is the
next big programming language,


WEBVTT
