01:13:57.266 --> 01:14:00.002 align:middle
&gt;&gt; Eight years ago, when
the iPhone was launched,


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

01:13:57.266 --> 01:14:00.002 align:middle
&gt;&gt; Eight years ago, when
the iPhone was launched,

01:14:00.002 --> 01:14:01.337 align:middle
it didn't have an App Store.

01:14:01.337 --> 01:14:06.509 align:middle
And there was tremendous desire
on the part of developers

01:14:06.509 --> 01:14:08.544 align:middle
and customers for Apple

01:14:08.544 --> 01:14:10.913 align:middle
to let third-party
applications be created.

01:14:10.913 --> 01:14:15.151 align:middle
We all had this dream
that apps were going

01:14:15.151 --> 01:14:19.522 align:middle
to become really important,
but it took some time

01:14:19.522 --> 01:14:22.625 align:middle
to realize how they would affect
everything that we care about,

01:14:22.625 --> 01:14:27.963 align:middle
and as that cumulative effect
appeared, then we all start

01:14:27.963 --> 01:14:30.099 align:middle
to realize, oh, my
goodness, this is bigger

01:14:30.099 --> 01:14:32.134 align:middle
than any of us imagined.

01:14:38.741 --> 01:14:41.344 align:middle
&gt;&gt; Apps plus handheld
devices,

01:14:41.344 --> 01:14:45.414 align:middle
I think that's a watershed
moment in civilization.

01:14:45.414 --> 01:14:46.916 align:middle
I put it up there
with the invention

01:14:46.916 --> 01:14:48.784 align:middle
of the microscope
and the telescope.

01:14:48.784 --> 01:14:56.158 align:middle
We live in a time where the most
powerful tools ever imagined

01:14:56.158 --> 01:15:00.129 align:middle
to investigate and probe
our world are in the hand


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

01:14:56.158 --> 01:15:00.129 align:middle
to investigate and probe
our world are in the hand

01:15:00.129 --> 01:15:02.264 align:middle
of essentially everyone.

01:15:03.666 --> 01:15:06.402 align:middle
&gt;&gt; If you think the Industrial
Revolution was transformational,

01:15:06.402 --> 01:15:08.437 align:middle
the App Store is way bigger.

01:15:08.437 --> 01:15:11.674 align:middle
I don't think we've seen
anything reach a mass adoption

01:15:11.674 --> 01:15:13.109 align:middle
at anything close to this pace.

01:15:13.109 --> 01:15:16.946 align:middle
It took, for example,
electricity over a hundred years

01:15:16.946 --> 01:15:19.348 align:middle
to get to its first
50 million users.

01:15:19.348 --> 01:15:22.852 align:middle
It took television 13
years, and the App Store got

01:15:22.852 --> 01:15:25.354 align:middle
to 50 million users
in only 17 months.

01:15:36.465 --> 01:15:38.868 align:middle
&gt;&gt; The thing the App
Store did was give each

01:15:38.868 --> 01:15:40.469 align:middle
and every developer a voice.

01:15:40.469 --> 01:15:44.140 align:middle
It's a testament that two
guys in a room working

01:15:44.140 --> 01:15:47.543 align:middle
on an idea can launch an app
and instantly have hundreds

01:15:47.543 --> 01:15:49.078 align:middle
of millions of people
very quickly.

01:15:49.078 --> 01:15:54.784 align:middle
The iPhone made photography
universally accessible.


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

01:16:00.389 --> 01:16:03.559 align:middle
&gt;&gt; I cannot think
of a single industry

01:16:03.559 --> 01:16:05.528 align:middle
that doesn't need an app.

01:16:05.528 --> 01:16:07.596 align:middle
People want data at
their fingertips.

01:16:07.596 --> 01:16:09.865 align:middle
They want personalized
experiences.

01:16:09.865 --> 01:16:13.202 align:middle
They want power over
their money.

01:16:13.202 --> 01:16:16.772 align:middle
And it's not just for banking;
it's for every industry.

01:16:16.772 --> 01:16:19.508 align:middle
The App Store has fundamentally
shifted how we all need

01:16:19.508 --> 01:16:20.342 align:middle
to deliver.

01:16:20.342 --> 01:16:23.412 align:middle
It's leveling the playing field.

01:16:26.415 --> 01:16:29.118 align:middle
&gt;&gt; We don't have to own
things.

01:16:29.118 --> 01:16:31.420 align:middle
We don't have to
own our own cars.

01:16:31.420 --> 01:16:33.489 align:middle
We don't have to
own our own music.

01:16:33.489 --> 01:16:37.226 align:middle
We can call it up
when we need it.

01:16:37.226 --> 01:16:39.495 align:middle
That's a big change, all
flowing from the idea

01:16:39.495 --> 01:16:42.264 align:middle
of not just convenience
but people building

01:16:42.264 --> 01:16:44.700 align:middle
up an infrastructure
around that.

01:16:44.700 --> 01:16:47.937 align:middle
We are now talking
not about hundreds

01:16:47.937 --> 01:16:52.208 align:middle
of people getting the benefits
of an idea, but millions.

01:16:57.246 --> 01:16:59.748 align:middle
&gt;&gt; If you had told me when I
was a kid that you would be able

01:16:59.748 --> 01:17:04.553 align:middle
to write an idea and then film
that idea and then distribute it


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

01:16:59.748 --> 01:17:04.553 align:middle
to write an idea and then film
that idea and then distribute it

01:17:04.553 --> 01:17:06.722 align:middle
to the world on a device
that you could also put

01:17:06.722 --> 01:17:10.092 align:middle
