in Apple Pay, Maps, and Siri.

01:22:31.613 --> 01:22:33.816 align:middle
Let's start with Timepiece.

01:22:33.816 --> 01:22:36.819 align:middle
Now, already, Apple Watch
is a really great timepiece,

01:22:36.819 --> 01:22:39.521 align:start
the most customizable one in the
world, and a lot of that is due

01:22:39.521 --> 01:22:41.757 align:middle
to the Watch faces and
how you can change them.

01:22:41.757 --> 01:22:44.927 align:middle
We are adding some new
Watch faces in watchOS 2.

01:22:44.927 --> 01:22:47.629 align:middle
That includes a beautiful
new Photos face to be able

01:22:47.629 --> 01:22:50.332 align:middle
to select any photo you have and
create a Watch face out of it.

01:22:50.332 --> 01:22:53.902 align:start
You can create more than one and
switch between them as you like.

01:22:53.902 --> 01:22:55.637 align:middle
Or you can select a photo album,

01:22:55.637 --> 01:22:56.972 align:middle
and every time you
raise your wrist,

01:22:56.972 --> 01:22:59.274 align:middle
you will see a different
photo from your album show up.

01:22:59.274 --> 01:23:02.444 align:middle
It's a great way of seeing
your photos throughout the day.


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

01:22:59.274 --> 01:23:02.444 align:middle
It's a great way of seeing
your photos throughout the day.

01:23:02.444 --> 01:23:04.880 align:middle
We went a little
further with this,

01:23:04.880 --> 01:23:06.315 align:middle
and we shot some
photos ourselves.

01:23:06.315 --> 01:23:07.850 align:middle
We did some time-lapse
photography

01:23:07.850 --> 01:23:10.419 align:middle
in some beautiful
locations around the world.

01:23:10.419 --> 01:23:12.321 align:middle
The way this works is
when you raise your wrist,

01:23:12.321 --> 01:23:14.590 align:middle
you will see this
24-hour shoot we have done

01:23:14.590 --> 01:23:17.426 align:middle
in different locations, and it
will be the current time there.

01:23:17.426 --> 01:23:19.328 align:middle
If it's in noon, you
will see noon in London.

01:23:19.328 --> 01:23:21.697 align:middle
If it's night, you'll
see Big Ben all lit up.

01:23:21.697 --> 01:23:23.065 align:middle
We've done this not
only for London,

01:23:23.065 --> 01:23:24.700 align:middle
but some other locations too.

01:23:24.700 --> 01:23:26.902 align:middle
You can choose from
Hong Kong, Mack Lake --

01:23:26.902 --> 01:23:28.570 align:middle
which a beautiful
place in the Sierras --

01:23:28.570 --> 01:23:32.107 align:middle
as well as New York,
Shanghai, and London.

01:23:32.107 --> 01:23:34.943 align:middle
It's a great way to see really
beautiful imagery, both your own

01:23:34.943 --> 01:23:36.678 align:middle
and these time-lapse
images, on your wrist.

01:23:36.678 --> 01:23:40.215 align:middle
You can customize your
Watch with these images

01:23:40.215 --> 01:23:42.317 align:middle
but you can also choose to
show the information that you

01:23:42.317 --> 01:23:44.853 align:middle
like on your Watch
face with something

01:23:44.853 --> 01:23:48.190 align:middle
in traditional Watch terms
that's called Complications.

01:23:48.190 --> 01:23:52.094 align:middle
With watchOS 2, we are really
excited to enable app developers

01:23:52.094 --> 01:23:54.329 align:middle
to make your own Complications.

01:23:54.329 --> 01:24:01.270 align:middle
[Applause]


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

01:23:54.329 --> 01:24:01.270 align:middle
[Applause]

01:24:01.270 --> 01:24:03.906 align:middle
So be able to do things
like show your flight time

01:24:03.906 --> 01:24:07.142 align:middle
from United, see the state
of your home control system,

01:24:07.142 --> 01:24:09.411 align:middle
look at the charge level
of your electric car,

01:24:09.411 --> 01:24:12.147 align:middle
or see sports scores, for
example, from the MLB app.

01:24:12.147 --> 01:24:13.715 align:middle
You can choose the
information that you most

01:24:13.715 --> 01:24:15.651 align:middle
like to see right
on your Watch face.

01:24:15.651 --> 01:24:17.419 align:middle
It's going to be
really, really cool.

01:24:17.419 --> 01:24:19.588 align:middle
And this will work not
only on the modular face

01:24:19.588 --> 01:24:21.990 align:middle
but across the others that
support Complications as well.

01:24:21.990 --> 01:24:24.393 align:middle
You will be able to choose
from a variety of templates,

01:24:24.393 --> 01:24:26.161 align:middle
and we'll make those
look beautiful in each

01:24:26.161 --> 01:24:28.063 align:middle
of the different Watch faces.

01:24:28.063 --> 01:24:29.464 align:middle
So it's going to be
a really fast way

01:24:29.464 --> 01:24:31.333 align:middle
to look at this information.

01:24:31.333 --> 01:24:32.434 align:middle
Now, we went further than this.

01:24:32.434 --> 01:24:34.102 align:middle
We thought it's really
great to be able

01:24:34.102 --> 01:24:35.804 align:middle
to see the current information,

01:24:35.804 --> 01:24:37.239 align:middle
but what about future
information,

01:24:37.239 --> 01:24:39.942 align:middle
like the weather later
today or your meeting

01:24:39.942 --> 01:24:41.910 align:middle
after the current one?

01:24:41.910 --> 01:24:44.079 align:middle
And what if you could go
forward in time and actually see

01:24:44.079 --> 01:24:46.848 align:middle
that information update
on your Watch face?

01:24:46.848 --> 01:24:48.617 align:middle
Well, we are supporting
that in watchOS 2

01:24:48.617 --> 01:24:51.420 align:middle
with something we
call Time Travel.

01:24:51.420 --> 01:24:53.722 align:middle
And you will be able to
rotate your Digital Crown,

01:24:53.722 --> 01:24:56.291 align:middle
and you can go both forward
and backward through time,

01:24:56.291 --> 01:24:59.428 align:middle
and the information will
update right on your screen.

01:24:59.428 --> 01:25:00.862 align:middle
Let's take a look here.


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

01:24:59.428 --> 01:25:00.862 align:middle
Let's take a look here.

01:25:00.862 --> 01:25:03.432 align:middle
So I've got my meeting in
the middle there and weather

01:25:03.432 --> 01:25:05.901 align:middle
and the charge level of
the car and time in London.

01:25:05.901 --> 01:25:08.670 align:middle
When I rotate the Crown, you
can see it's changing the time

01:25:08.670 --> 01:25:10.906 align:middle
and showing me things
that are coming up.

01:25:10.906 --> 01:25:13.075 align:middle
Now, we know a really popular
one here might be the stocks

01:25:13.075 --> 01:25:15.243 align:middle
Complication, but we
haven't cracked that one yet.

01:25:15.243 --> 01:25:19.147 align:middle
We are working on it.

01:25:19.147 --> 01:25:21.116 align:middle
You can keep rotating,
keep going forward,

01:25:21.116 --> 01:25:22.451 align:middle
get all the way to tonight.

01:25:22.451 --> 01:25:24.353 align:middle
You can see I have a date
night tonight, weather is going

01:25:24.353 --> 01:25:27.022 align:start
to be good, time in London will
be 2:00 a.m. You can see all the

01:25:27.022 --> 01:25:30.192 align:middle
information you like to see in
the time you want to look at it.

01:25:30.192 --> 01:25:32.694 align:middle
Really, really fun
way to interact

01:25:32.694 --> 01:25:35.063 align:middle
with time on your Watch.

01:25:35.063 --> 01:25:37.432 align:middle
That's Time Travel.

01:25:37.432 --> 01:25:42.871 align:middle
[Applause]

01:25:42.871 --> 01:25:45.540 align:middle
Now, we also thought, What
would be a great experience

01:25:45.540 --> 01:25:48.243 align:middle
for the Watch when it's on
your nightstand and charging?

01:25:48.243 --> 01:25:50.345 align:middle
Well, we've come up with a
new user interface for this

01:25:50.345 --> 01:25:52.981 align:middle
in watchOS 2 called
Nightstand Mode.

01:25:52.981 --> 01:25:55.183 align:middle
When you put your Watch on
its side and it's charging,

01:25:55.183 --> 01:25:57.652 align:middle
you will get this beautiful
display now of the time,

01:25:57.652 --> 01:25:59.688 align:middle
and of course, you can set
an alarm that will wake you

01:25:59.688 --> 01:26:03.191 align:middle
up in the morning, and it
will go something like this.


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

01:25:59.688 --> 01:26:03.191 align:middle
up in the morning, and it
will go something like this.

01:26:03.191 --> 01:26:05.394 align:middle
[Alarm tone]

01:26:05.394 --> 01:26:07.496 align:middle
So a beautiful little
bedside alarm clock now

01:26:07.496 --> 01:26:10.065 align:middle
with Apple Watch, and
the buttons on the side

01:26:10.065 --> 01:26:13.602 align:middle
and the Crown act as your
Snooze and your Off button.

01:26:13.602 --> 01:26:17.105 align:middle
A really fun way to have a
Nightstand view on your Watch.

01:26:17.105 --> 01:26:19.808 align:middle
Those are some of the great
new Timepiece functions

01:26:19.808 --> 01:26:22.377 align:middle
that are coming in watchOS 2.

01:26:22.377 --> 01:26:23.979 align:middle
Let's look at communication.

01:26:23.979 --> 01:26:25.347 align:middle
Now, already Apple
Watch is great

01:26:25.347 --> 01:26:27.015 align:middle
at communicating
with your friends.

01:26:27.015 --> 01:26:30.052 align:middle
You can just press the side
button and see your 12 friends

01:26:30.052 --> 01:26:31.420 align:middle
that you have selected.

01:26:31.420 --> 01:26:33.555 align:middle
Now, we realize that some of
you have more than 12 friends,

01:26:33.555 --> 01:26:36.558 align:middle
so now in watchOS 2, you
can have different sets

01:26:36.558 --> 01:26:39.227 align:middle
of friends you can select,
and you can add a friend right

01:26:39.227 --> 01:26:41.129 align:middle
from your Watch by
pressing the plus sign

01:26:41.129 --> 01:26:43.732 align:middle
and add a friend right there.

01:26:43.732 --> 01:26:45.500 align:middle
Isn't that cool?

01:26:45.500 --> 01:26:48.570 align:middle
[Applause]

01:26:48.570 --> 01:26:49.938 align:middle
Now, when you are
communicating with someone,

01:26:49.938 --> 01:26:52.574 align:middle
you can make a phone call or
send a message or send a drawing

01:26:52.574 --> 01:26:55.677 align:middle
with Digital Touch, and now
in watchOS 2, you will be able

01:26:55.677 --> 01:26:57.546 align:middle
to use multiple colors
in your drawings,

01:26:57.546 --> 01:26:59.481 align:middle
so you can draw a
beautiful flower

01:26:59.481 --> 01:27:01.883 align:middle
that has more than
just one color.


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

01:26:59.481 --> 01:27:01.883 align:middle
that has more than
just one color.

01:27:01.883 --> 01:27:05.387 align:middle
Even my drawings are starting
to look better now with this.

01:27:05.387 --> 01:27:06.455 align:middle
Also an email.

01:27:06.455 --> 01:27:08.123 align:middle
You can already read
email on your Watch.

01:27:08.123 --> 01:27:11.526 align:middle
With watchOS 2, you will
be able to reply to email.

01:27:11.526 --> 01:27:16.064 align:middle
[Applause]

01:27:16.064 --> 01:27:17.933 align:middle
And with the phone, you can
already take phone calls

01:27:17.933 --> 01:27:19.034 align:middle
on your Watch.

01:27:19.034 --> 01:27:20.502 align:middle
We are now going to
support FaceTime Audio,

01:27:20.502 --> 01:27:22.537 align:middle
so you will get really
high-fidelity calls right

01:27:22.537 --> 01:27:23.538 align:middle
on your wrist.

01:27:23.538 --> 01:27:28.343 align:middle
[Applause]

01:27:28.343 --> 01:27:29.911 align:middle
And with Health &amp; Fitness,

01:27:29.911 --> 01:27:32.848 align:middle
already Apple Watch is a great
partner for Health &amp; Fitness.

01:27:32.848 --> 01:27:36.251 align:middle
With watchOS 2, we are enabling
your favorite fitness apps

01:27:36.251 --> 01:27:37.853 align:middle
to run natively on the Watch

01:27:37.853 --> 01:27:40.889 align:middle
so you can use them wherever
you are, and your workouts

01:27:40.889 --> 01:27:42.991 align:middle
with these apps will
contribute directly

01:27:42.991 --> 01:27:45.360 align:middle
to your all-day activity,
which will be really great,

01:27:45.360 --> 01:27:47.562 align:middle
so if you go on a bike
ride, it will count.

01:27:47.562 --> 01:27:50.465 align:middle
[Applause]

01:27:50.465 --> 01:27:52.934 align:middle
We are also enabling
Siri to start workouts,

01:27:52.934 --> 01:27:55.137 align:middle
so you can just raise your
wrist and say, hey, Siri,

01:27:55.137 --> 01:27:56.538 align:middle
start a 30-minute
run in the park,

01:27:56.538 --> 01:27:59.608 align:middle
and it will start the Workout
app and get it going for you.

01:27:59.608 --> 01:28:03.211 align:middle
You can also say things like
"go for a 300-calorie bike ride"


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

01:27:59.608 --> 01:28:03.211 align:middle
You can also say things like
"go for a 300-calorie bike ride"

01:28:03.211 --> 01:28:06.515 align:middle
or "go for a 5-mile run, "
and it will start the workout

01:28:06.515 --> 01:28:08.550 align:middle
for you without having to
touch the watch at all.

01:28:08.550 --> 01:28:10.118 align:middle
When you achieve something,

01:28:10.118 --> 01:28:12.721 align:middle
there are some beautiful new
achievements you will see

01:28:12.721 --> 01:28:14.189 align:middle
that look like this.

01:28:14.189 --> 01:28:15.957 align:middle
They spin right in, they're
beautiful, you can play

01:28:15.957 --> 01:28:17.826 align:middle
with them in 3D on the
Watch, they are engraved

01:28:17.826 --> 01:28:20.962 align:middle
on the back now with your
name, and you can share these

01:28:20.962 --> 01:28:24.065 align:middle
with people over Messages,
Facebook, or Twitter.

01:28:24.065 --> 01:28:28.603 align:middle
Really cool Health &amp;
Fitness.

01:28:28.603 --> 01:28:31.940 align:middle
[Applause]

01:28:31.940 --> 01:28:33.441 align:middle
With Apple Pay, you saw some

01:28:33.441 --> 01:28:35.143 align:middle
of the great new
support we are bringing

01:28:35.143 --> 01:28:36.645 align:middle
for store cards and
rewards cards.

01:28:36.645 --> 01:28:38.213 align:middle
We are supporting
that in the Watch,

01:28:38.213 --> 01:28:40.815 align:middle
so you can select a store card
and use it right in your Watch

01:28:40.815 --> 01:28:42.951 align:middle
in a merchant terminal
just by waving it

01:28:42.951 --> 01:28:44.085 align:middle
at the store stand there.

01:28:44.085 --> 01:28:46.955 align:middle
And with Wallet coming to Watch,

01:28:46.955 --> 01:28:48.690 align:middle
all of your rewards cards
will be right there,

01:28:48.690 --> 01:28:50.659 align:middle
and you can also use those
right from your Watch

01:28:50.659 --> 01:28:52.494 align:middle
as you are doing purchases.

01:28:52.494 --> 01:28:54.796 align:middle
With Transit, we are
supporting, of course,

01:28:54.796 --> 01:28:57.599 align:middle
the mass transit capabilities
in Maps now, so you will be able

01:28:57.599 --> 01:28:59.467 align:middle
to see the transit
lines on your wrist.

01:28:59.467 --> 01:29:01.102 align:middle
You can actually see
the departure times


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

01:28:59.467 --> 01:29:01.102 align:middle
You can actually see
the departure times

01:29:01.102 --> 01:29:02.704 align:middle
for different stations
you are near.

01:29:02.704 --> 01:29:05.407 align:middle
When you are navigating, you
will get step-by-step directions

01:29:05.407 --> 01:29:08.410 align:middle
about getting through the
different mass transit you use.

01:29:08.410 --> 01:29:11.580 align:middle
With Siri, we are continuing
to add new domains for Siri.

01:29:11.580 --> 01:29:13.782 align:middle
In watchOS 2, we
are enabling Siri

01:29:13.782 --> 01:29:16.184 align:middle
to get you mass transit
directions, like bus directions

01:29:16.184 --> 01:29:17.953 align:middle
to the Ferry Building,
which will look like this

01:29:17.953 --> 01:29:19.654 align:middle
and you can just
start navigating.

01:29:19.654 --> 01:29:22.390 align:middle
Or you can control things
in your home with Siri,

01:29:22.390 --> 01:29:25.093 align:middle
you can say things like "hey
Siri set the dinner scene,"

01:29:25.093 --> 01:29:27.562 align:middle
and it will talk to any
HomeKit-enabled devices

01:29:27.562 --> 01:29:30.532 align:middle
in your house and set the
lights just how you want them.

01:29:30.532 --> 01:29:32.834 align:middle
Isn't that cool?

01:29:32.834 --> 01:29:34.669 align:middle
It's going to be great.

01:29:34.669 --> 01:29:38.206 align:middle
[Applause]

01:29:38.206 --> 01:29:40.375 align:middle
Another great thing is you
can actually ask for any

01:29:40.375 --> 01:29:43.011 align:middle
of the Glances you have,
so you can say "hey, Siri,

01:29:43.011 --> 01:29:45.180 align:middle
show me the Instagram
Glance," and it will show

01:29:45.180 --> 01:29:46.514 align:middle
up right on your Watch face.

01:29:46.514 --> 01:29:49.017 align:middle
This could be a glance you
don't have currently selected.

01:29:49.017 --> 01:29:50.885 align:middle
It's a great way
to show information

01:29:50.885 --> 01:29:54.456 align:middle
from third-party apps
right there in Siri.

01:29:54.456 --> 01:29:55.890 align:middle
So those are just
some of the highlights

01:29:55.890 --> 01:29:57.325 align:middle
of what's coming in watchOS 2.

01:29:57.325 --> 01:29:58.326 align:middle
We think it's going
to be a really,

01:29:58.326 --> 01:30:01.429 align:middle
really great update
to the Watch.


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

01:29:58.326 --> 01:30:01.429 align:middle
really great update
to the Watch.

01:30:01.429 --> 01:30:02.697 align:middle
Now, that's not all.

01:30:02.697 --> 01:30:06.635 align:middle
[Applause]

01:30:06.635 --> 01:30:09.938 align:middle
We also, of course, focused on
what we can do for developers,

01:30:09.938 --> 01:30:12.907 align:middle
and already, out of the gate
on day one, you can build apps

01:30:12.907 --> 01:30:15.210 align:middle
for Apple Watch using
something called WatchKit,

01:30:15.210 --> 01:30:19.147 align:middle
and that has enabled many
thousands of apps now

01:30:19.147 --> 01:30:22.384 align:middle
to be created for Apple Watch,
and these apps today function

01:30:22.384 --> 01:30:24.019 align:middle
by relying on your phone.

01:30:24.019 --> 01:30:26.154 align:middle
So you might have, for
example, an app on your Watch

01:30:26.154 --> 01:30:28.256 align:middle
and the user interface
runs on your phone

01:30:28.256 --> 01:30:30.892 align:middle
and the user interface is on
your Watch, but all the logic

01:30:30.892 --> 01:30:33.328 align:middle
for your app today
runs on your phone.

01:30:33.328 --> 01:30:35.964 align:middle
With native apps, you will
be able to move that logic

01:30:35.964 --> 01:30:38.667 align:middle
to the watch so both the
UI and the logic are there,

01:30:38.667 --> 01:30:41.303 align:middle
it will all run locally,
performance will be great,

01:30:41.303 --> 01:30:42.671 align:middle
responsiveness will be great,

01:30:42.671 --> 01:30:45.040 align:middle
it's going to be a great new
frontier for apps on Apple Watch

01:30:45.040 --> 01:30:46.741 align:middle
with native app support.

01:30:46.741 --> 01:30:53.214 align:middle
[Applause]

01:30:53.214 --> 01:30:56.117 align:start
When you are actually wandering
away from your phone sometimes,

01:30:56.117 --> 01:30:57.686 align:middle
your apps will be able
to communicate directly

01:30:57.686 --> 01:30:59.721 align:middle
with the network with
known Wi-Fi networks,

01:30:59.721 --> 01:31:01.690 align:middle
so you can get the information
you want wherever you are


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

01:30:59.721 --> 01:31:01.690 align:middle
so you can get the information
you want wherever you are

01:31:01.690 --> 01:31:03.758 align:middle
with your Watch.

01:31:03.758 --> 01:31:07.929 align:middle
[Applause]

01:31:07.929 --> 01:31:10.065 align:middle
So we heard from you as we
were working on native apps,

01:31:10.065 --> 01:31:11.866 align:middle
a lot of feature requests
of things you would

01:31:11.866 --> 01:31:13.001 align:middle
like to do on the Watch.

01:31:13.001 --> 01:31:15.003 align:middle
These are a bunch of the
things that we've heard.

01:31:15.003 --> 01:31:16.471 align:middle
So we've been listening to that.

